opy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/c34c8905-dd22-4adc-a5ac-668ab4932e81-copy.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Transcend features extensive connectivity options, including a pair of HDMI 2.1 ports, a 2.1 Display port, three USB-A ports for peripherals, and a 3.5 mm audio jack for headphones. You’ll also find a trio of USB-C ports: Two are capable of handling data throughput, while the third can deliver up to 140W of power, and is reserved for displays or laptops.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003ePerhaps the coolest feature of the Transcend, however, is its ability to display two sources simultaneously with its picture-in-picture mode, effectively giving you two screens at once and allowing you to seamlessly swap between them. Oh, and the back of the monitor has built-in RGB lighting, in case you needed to make an even bigger statement.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"757\" data-pswp-width=\"1473\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A stock image of the ports found on the back of the HP Omen Transcend gaming monitor\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-15-151044.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: HP\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe included stand is height, tilt, and swivel adjustable, but it can also rotate 90 degrees into a portrait orientation. However, if you prefer to use a hydraulic arm or similar mounting solution, the monitor features a 100 x 100 VESA mount.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhile the list of included features are impressive, just note that unless your desktop is pushing the latest hardware or you’ve scaled down the resolution of whatever you’re playing, it’s unlikely you’ll be able to actually hit 240 frames per second. But if you need a monitor that can do it all and then some, you could do a lot worse than the HP Omen Transcend, especially at this price.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cform\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch2\u003eShopkeeper\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePolygon’s handpicked deals on games, movies, books, and more.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/form\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
